    {
      "turn": 23,
      "message": "[GM] Uneventful night. Morning wake-up. Long rest: all members HP/MP full.",
      "narrative": "The night was quiet.\n\nThe mana wire vibrated faintly a couple of times, but it was only small wild animals passing through. The campfire gradually died down, and stars filled the sky.\n\nAt shift change, Lucena approached Noel and whispered softly.\n\"That hooded one was only pretending to sleep. Tell Saiki too.\"\nNoel nodded and gripped his axe. Lucena clutched her daggers to her chest and fell into a light sleep.\n\nAt dawn. Noel detected movement in the darkness. The hooded figure quietly rose and slipped out of the rest stop, returning shortly after. When they returned, he could see them wiping their hands on their clothes.\n\nBefore long, dawn broke.\n\nWith birdsong and morning sunlight illuminating the rest stop, Saiki opened his eyes. The mana wire's sensation had faded — its effect had expired. His body felt light. A full night's sleep had completely restored his mana.\n\nNoel looked toward Saiki and said briefly.\n\"...The hooded one went out once at dawn.\"\n\nLooking around, the hooded figure's spot was empty. No one knew when they had left. The swordsman was still leaning against the wall with his sword in his arms, and the peddler was packing up and preparing to depart.\n\nHallan said while watering the pack horse.\n\"...We can leave in about an hour. We'll reach Karendel today.\"",
      "user_input": "",
      "dialogues": [
        {
          "speaker": "lucena",
          "target": "noel",
          "line": "That hooded one was only pretending to sleep. Tell Saiki too.",
          "tone": "whisper",
          "type": "whisper"
        },
        {
          "speaker": "noel",
          "target": "saiki",
          "line": "...The hooded one went out once at dawn.",
          "tone": "calm",
          "type": "dialogue"
        },
        {
          "speaker": "hallan",
          "line": "...We can leave in about an hour. We'll reach Karendel today.",
          "tone": "calm",
          "type": "dialogue"
        }
      ],
      "timestamp": "09:43:13",
      "archived_at": "2026-03-28"
    },
    {
      "turn": 24,
      "message": "[GM] Peddler/swordsman join as travel companions. Departure toward Karendel.",
      "narrative": "Saiki approached the peddler packing his things and the swordsman leaning against the wall.\n\n\"We're heading to Karendel. If you're going the same way, would you like to travel together?\"\n\nThe peddler frantically gathered his bundle and nodded repeatedly.\n\"Oh my, I was just worried about going alone! If you'd join me, nothing could be more welcome...\"\n\nThe swordsman, still in his position leaning against the wall with his hand on his sword, regarded Saiki for a moment.\n\"...Karendel.\"\nAfter a brief silence, he slowly stood up.\n\"I happen to have business that way. We merely share the same road, so don't mind me.\"\n\nHe glanced at the empty spot where the hooded figure had been, but said nothing.\n\nHallan said while hitching the pack horse.\n\"...No reason to object. The more of us there are, the less beasts will bother us.\"\n\nLucena sidled up to Saiki and whispered.\n\"The peddler is whatever, but that swordsman... he was really good at muffling his footsteps while pretending to sleep. He might not be a thief, but he's not ordinary either.\"\n\nNoel chimed in while slinging his axe over his shoulder.\n\"Having one more guy who can use a blade makes things a bit easier for me.\"\n\nThe party had grown. Hallan patted the pack horse's back, and the cart began to move slowly. Morning mist lay thin over the trade road. Half a day or so until Karendel.",
